Product Description:
Pill Buddy Naturals makes pill time a rewarding and easy experience for you and your pet. Pill Buddy Naturals will accommodate almost any size pill or capsule intended for dogs - simply ‘push, squeeze and feed’.

Pill Buddy Naturals is ‘marinated’ in an exclusive blend of natural ingredients called Nature’s SauceTM. Nature’s SauceTM provides excellent mouth-feel, impact and texture; providing a unique surface for the treat to be swallowed whole. This prevents the dog from bitting into bitter tasting medicine and spitting it out.

Pill Buddy Naturals are conveniently wrapped in pairs to preserve freshness and functionality and prevent drying and cracking.

After the dog finishes its medication, Pill Buddy Naturals can continue to be fed as a delicious soft and chewy treat for all occasions.

***Like natural peanut butter, oil separation can occur with Pill Buddy Naturals. This is normal and is not a defect. We choose not to use artificial chemicals. As a result, the healthy blend of oils and fats in Nature’s Sauce is super yummy and creates a great feeling in the dog’s mouth that they love.***

A gentle ear cleaning lotion formulated by an herbal scientist using only premium botanicals.

The inside of your dog’s ear is warm and moist. It’s a perfect breeding ground for bacteria. Ears All Right™ is an all natural botanical formula that works to break down and remove wax, dirt, and foreign debris. Reduces inflammation, irritation, and helps treat mite infestation. Helps heal and prevent infection from minor scratches and insect bites.  Relieves issues associated with yeast infections, excessive wax build up, ear odor, and allergies.

Remember...healthy pet ears have no smell!

For pets with sensitive, inflamed, or encrusted ears.

INITIAL USE: Squeeze 5 – 10 drops directly into the ear canal.  Allow to soak, and then attempt to clean ear with clean cotton ball. Repeat 2 – 3 times a day as needed.

MAINTENANCE: Squeeze onto cotton ball and gently clean and swab ear and ear canal. Clean ear internally and externally. Do not use the same cotton ball or swab in each ear. Always clean pets ears after swimming and bathing and when pet has been playing in insect ridden area.

Never insert swabs or sharp objects into pet’s ears.

Active Ingredients:

  • Aloe Vera Gel (whole leaf)
  • Isopropanol USP
  • Glycerine 99.5%
  • Calendula extract
  • Rosemary extract
  • Myrrh extract
  • Cinnamon oil

Inactive Ingredients:

  • De-ionized water

Gentle eye wash formulated to soothe and maintain healthy eyes.  Eyes so Bright™ is great for removing foreign debris and encrustation that build up in the mucous membranes of your pet's eyes.  Active ingredients include aloe, goldenseal, and echinacea.

RECOMMENDED USE:

To remove encrustations & foreign debris. For dogs and cats 12 weeks and older.

INITIAL USE:
 
Pour onto clean cotton ball, place over eye area and allow Eyes So Bright™ to seep into eye area. Repeat 2 times per day for several days or until there is improvement.
 
MAINTENANCE:
 
Use Eyes So Bright™ once each week. To avoid transferring infection, do not use the same cotton ball in each eye.
 
INGREDIENTS:

Active Ingredients:

  • Aloe Vera Juice (traditional hand fillet HF, FG)
  • Witch hazel
  • Goldenseal golden extract
  • Gotu kola fluid extract
  • Echinacea fluid extract

Inactive Ingredients:

  • De-ionized water

Formulated with the highest quality botanicals, Happy Traveler was designed by a holistic veterinarian and PhD herbal scientist to ease anxiety and motion sickness. Useful for separation anxiety, travel anxiety, to socialize a nervous or excitable pet into a new environment, during thunderstorms, fireworks, airline travel, visits to groomers, and kennels. With your Vet’s approval, helps your pet during recovery from surgery/injury by relaxing them to minimize chewing on bandages and sutures. Non-habit forming. No harmful side effects when used as directed. Made in the USA.

Recommended Use:
Up to 25 lbs- 1 capsule
Up to 75 lbs- 2 capsules                             
Over 75 lbs- 3 capsules
For dogs and cats 12 weeks and older.

Home Alone

A calming remedy for cats and dogs that get anxious when left alone.    

 

Separation anxiety if one of the most common social disorders among dogs and occurs among cats as well. As soon as you took your pet home, that pet started to form a bond with you that continued to grow. That bond is important in a healthy relationship between you and your pet, but when your pet becomes too dependant problems can arise.  

 

Dogs with separation anxiety often act out when they are left home alone. You might come home to find your dog has destroyed furniture, defecated on the floor and barked all day long. Your dog may also whine and show signs of depression in your absence. Often dogs with separation anxiety will also become over-excited upon the return of their owners.

 

Cats can also experience separation anxiety, though it is not as common as it is in dogs. Symptoms are often less noticeable than they are in dogs, as anxious cats tend to be less destructive. If you notice your cat is exhibiting saddened behaviours every time you prepare to leave the house, or is excessively attached to you when you are home then your cat may have anxiety issues. Like dogs, cats with separation anxiety may forget about their house training when you are gone.

 

Treating separation anxiety in your pets involves reducing stress or panic they feel without your presence. It is not a matter of reducing the bond that you share. The herbs found in Home Alone are calming herbs that help your pet relax. They can help your pets to stay happy when you aren’t around, so you don’t have to worry about leaving them at home.

Stress Relief

Traditionally used as a sedative for relief of restlessness or nervousness. It is also anti-viral, antifungal and anti-inflammatory. NaturPet Stress Relief contains only one medicinal ingredient, St. John’s Wort. St. John’s Wort has been used for the treatment of stress and anxiety. It is also commonly used as an antidepressant. Humans have used it for millennia and we believe that if it is good enough for you, it is good enough for your cat or dog.

 

St. John’s Wort can relieve pain and is ideal in the treatment of anxiety, nervous tension and other depressive-type symptoms. St. John’s Wort helps calm your pet while restoring normal, healthy energy levels and vitality.

 

Your cat or dog is important to you and you do everything you can to ensure your pet has a good life. You provide for your cat or dog as best as you can, however, sometimes life is just stressful for a cat or dog.

 

Your cat or dog may experience stress as a result of environmental factors. Change can be hard for your cat or dog. Remember when you first picked up your new friend from the breeder or pet store? It was probably a hard transition for your cat or dog. A new home, new family members (including other pets), thunderstorms, fireworks, a visit to the kennel or getting lost in an unfamiliar area can all cause stress for your cat or dog. When your cat or dog becomes removed from the comfortable environment you provide, or that environment changes, your pet may feel stress.

 

Stress causes a rise in a cat or dog’s physiological state. The heart rate increases, breathing becomes heavy and the cat or dog may begin to quiver or shake. Your cat or dog’s “Fight or flight” instincts can kick in, which might be dangerous, as they try to avoid the perceived danger. Your cat or dog may pace the house, hide out, be excessively vocal and become restless. You know your pet the best, so be sure to watch for unusual behaviours that could be the result of your cat or dog being stressed. Stress can be the result of seemingly small environmental changes; it’s up to you to make sure your cat or dog is adjusting properly.

Product Description:
Cool those hot spots! A fantastic first aid ointment to treat your pet's wounds, cuts, scrapes, boils, burns, bites and abscesses - Prevents infection and promotes healing.    

 

 

"I have been using your NaturPet Skin Mend for several months with good results.

The ointment has been used to treat my dog “Charlie” who suffers from an allergy which results in him scratching, causing redness and severe irritation.  The ointment does offer relief.

Thank you"

D.B from Kelowna

Healthy Lungs

Many pets – especially very young and older pets – are prone to catching respiratory infections, similar to colds in humans. Respiratory aids can assist with preventing and treating all types of respiratory problems.

A cough medicine for your pets! Clears your pet's lungs and controls dry coughing. Great for asthma, bronchitis and kennel cough.

Digest It

Poor appetite and low energy? This digestive aid will help to improve your pet's digestive function and boost metabolism.

 

INGREDIENTS

Dandelion root (Taraxacum officinale)

Dandelion roots and leaves have been used for centuries as cleansing agents for the kidneys, gallbladder and liver and are a rich source of organic vitamins and minerals. The primary beneficial constituents found in the dandelion are the bitter principles called sesquiterpene lactones, which are unique to this plant. These bitter principles stimulate digestion and act as a mild laxative. The increase of bile production of the gallbladder and bile flow from the liver helps to stimulate sluggish liver function and increase dietary fat metabolism in your pet’s body. By improving fat digestion and utilization a change will often be seen in the lustre and shine of fur.

EAR Drops


This herbal formula has been used successfully for decades as an effective treatment for many kinds of ear conditions including outer and middle ear infection. Other major uses include:

  • Ear discharge
  • Infection
  • Vertigo from middle ear inflammation
  • This popular blend provides fast relief for itchy, aching or infected ears.

Arthritis Relief

It hurts to see your pet suffering from arthritis. Arthritis Relief promotes healing and relieves pain so you and your pet will feel better!                

Cats and dogs can suffer from arthritis just as humans can, which can cause a serious detriment to your cat or dog’s lifestyle. Arthritis is a common ailment among cats and dogs, especially those cats and dogs who are overweight or who have had previous injuries such as fractures or hip dysplasia.

While arthritis is common in cats and dogs, it can easily be misdiagnosed. Perhaps you have noticed that your cat or dog is spending more time sleeping and less time playing. Your cat or dog may be gaining weight or experiencing mood changes. If you notice this in your cat or dog, you might assume your best friend has a cold or the flu, however it may be arthritis and you should have your cat or dog checked by the vet. Hot or swollen joints, limping or favouring a limb and avoiding running and jumping may also be signs of arthritis in your cat or dog.

Product Description: PET Medicine dropper bottles

Canine Friendly Pet First Aid Kit lets you assist your pet's injuries to ease his suffering until you can consult your veterinarian. The 32 items in this bright orange, easy-to-see kit are organized into clear vinyl pockets for quick, easy access. The outer nylon case is bright orange with reflective piping, so is easy to locate. A first aid manual is included to provide easy-to-follow directions. Loops on zipper let you open the case easily while wearing gloves. The belt loop on the back of case lets you wear it conveniently on your belt. Take it with you when hiking, hunting, or on any other outdoor adventure. Keep one around the house, too, for everyday use.

32-item Kit Includes:

  • 4 Gauze pads (3" x 3")     
  • 4 Gauze pads (2" x 3")
  • 3 Gauze rolls (PBT Bandage)     
  • 1 Roll first aid tape
  • 1 Tweezers     
  • 1 Blunt tip scissors
  • 1 Pair Latex free exam gloves     
  • 1 Saline solution (20 ml)
  • 8 Antiseptic wipes     
  • 2 Wooden Tongue Depressors
  • 1 Instant cold pack     
  • 1 Reusable woven cloth triangle bandage
  • 2 Patch adhesive bandages     
  • 1 Elastic bandage
  • 1 Emergency blanket     


Kit also includes Walks 'N' Wags Pet First Aid Manual, which gives you easy-to-follow directions.

NUPRO Joint Support Dog Supplement has Glucosamine complex, MSM and Ester-C* , which enriches the original formula, especially for the active dog. Your dog now has the benefit of a scientifically balanced formula that is rich in vitamins, minerals, enzymes, amino acids and essential fatty acids along with the extra ingredients to support normal joint function.

NUPRO provides the necessary raw nutrients (lacking from cooked and processed dog foods) with easily digestible whole foods, specially designed to condition your dog from the inside out!

NUPRO Joint Support is not just for senior dogs or those with arthritis! The active athletes, show dogs, working dogs, police and search and rescue canines, sled dogs, hunting dogs, AND large breed dogs, as well, will profit from having glucosamine in their diet. The combination of NUPRO's raw formula with the added extras make for a superior product from which ALL adult dogs will benefit.

Glucosamine Complex (500 mg. per scoop) is our own special formula that is an easily absorbed natural substance that stimulates the production of proteoglycans which help to maintain the health and resiliency of connective tissues and restores the damaged cells of cartilage tissue. Glucosamine complex helps promote the synovial fluid that lubricates the joints.

MSM (300 mg. per scoop) is a natural source of bioavailable sulfur, essential for the growth and repair of tendons, cartilage and other connective tissues. MSM is also an anti-inflammatory agent.

Ester-C Chelated Mineral Blend (300 mg. per scoop) boosts the absorption of the glucosamine complex and MSM and promotes collagen formation.

NUPRO Joint Support also contains Norwegian kelp, flaxseed, nutritional yeast culture, desiccated liver, bee pollen, garlic, calcium citrate, lecithin and lactobacillus acidophilus.

NUPRO is made with fresh, premium ingredients that are human-grade quality. NUPRO does NOT contain any preservatives, sugar, fillers, corn, wheat, grains, or by-products.

The Dog Miracle Puzzle is a mentally challenging treat puzzle game for you and your dog, which can be varied endlessly by how you place the puzzle bricks and where you put the treats. You decide how hard it is going to be. 

Hide treats in all the recesses in both the bottom and the upper side of all the bricks in the puzzle, stack the bricks on top of each other and lock them in different directions. Let the dog look for the treats by trying to move, lift, or push aside brick after brick with its paw or nose.

The game can be varied and laid out in several different ways for different degrees of difficulty, from easy to little more advanced, by laying the bricks in different directions, turned upwards or downwards, to the left or the right and across each other.

Increase the degree of difficulty: By putting the Dog Miracle Puzzle on a stool, or a chair or in your lap, which means that the dog cannot use its paw but only its nose, which is usually a little harder….

A few tips… You If the dog tries to bite the game or the parts, put your hand over it and pause. When the dog has calmed down, say “Go on” and let the dog try again. If the dog keeps trying to bite, teach it to work only with its paw. If the dog wants instead to dive into the game and thrash about with its paw, teach it to work with its nose by putting the game on a stool/chair appropriate to the size of the dog, which is also practical if the dog is injured, e.g. in a paw, or has recently had an operation.

 

Important… Do not let the dog/cat chew or bite the toy, only play the game with the dog/cat, do not leave the dog/cat unsupervised, do not let the dog/cat play with or chew the bricks/parts. When you have finished playing, put the toy away. It is meant only for animals, it is not a toy for children.

Note!... Use the covers only for dogs that can cope with small parts without chewing them to pieces.

Have fun!

Product Description: Bully Sticks are a great way to give your pet something to chew on that they'll love and is great for them too. All of our bull sticks for dogs promote healthy teeth and gums, and are made from free-ranging Brazilian cattle, so you don't have to worry about how safe they are. Available in sizes from 6" to 24", all of our bully sticks are 100% beef, meaning your dog will actually digest them, unlike their old rawhide chews.

Yappetizers was founded in 2003, is proudly 100% Canadian owned and operates out the Lower Mainland of British Columbia Their mission is to offer wholesome dog & cat treats of uncompromising quality, promote good health and well-being for pets everywhere and grow a progressive business…naturally!

From grassy plains and green mountain pastures, down rivers and streams to the sweet salty smell of the ocean. All products come from an environment of crisp air and clean water. Only wild fish and meat cuts that are free of steroids, hormones and antibiotics are used. The treats are naturally preserved through the age old process of drying, and are high in both nutrients and quality.

A great everyday dog walking harness with plastic quick-release buckles that make it quick to get on and off.

The harness is quick and easy to put on - simply slip it over your dog’s head and then clip the Quick Release Buckles around the midsection. The five different adjustment points provide a near-custom fit.

An effective walking harness to eliminate the choking and pulling experienced with just a collar, the Tru-Fit Smart Harness features a halt ring on the chest plate. If your pup attempts to pull on a leash attached to the halt ring, it will just turn him around effectively training him that pulling will get him nowhere! The chest pad provides ultimate comfort by reducing stress on the trachea and sternum while dispersing kinetic energy across the chest of the dog.

The harness can also be used in the car as a dog restraint, preventing distracted driving accidents.

Includes 10-inch lead which can be attached via carabiner to any harness for training or attached to your car seatbelt system to restrain your dog while driving.

  • Great everyday dog walking harness
  • Weinramener plastic quick-release buckles make it easy to get on and off
  • Five adjustment points for a perfect fit on all shapes and sizes 
  • Broad, padded chest plate ensures comfort
  • No-pull harness with halt ring on chest
  • Can be used in car travel as a restraint to prevent distracted driving
  • Includes a 10-inch lead for training or to use as a dog seat belt loop to prevent distracted driving
  • Compatible with all Kurgo vehicle restraint systems such as Direct to Seat Belt Tether, Swivel Tether and the Auto Zip Line
  • Machine washable. Line dry.

Size Chart 

Measure chest and neck to determine harness size. The fit should be snug but not restrictive.

Recommended Accessories

Direct to Seat Belt Tether: This dog seat belt attaches to your dog’s harness with a carabiner and clicks directly into the female slot of any car’s seat belt, making it quick and easy to restrain your pup to avoid distracted driving.

Swivel Tether: Our strongest tether system, featuring a carabiner used by arborists. Its swivel action also makes it harder for those escape artist pups to get free from their restraint or twist their seat belt tether.

Our customers tell us, time and again, that their cats become healthier, happier and more alert on GO!™ recipes. So GO!™ was created to be a complete, nutrient-packed food that puts more "life" into everyday cats.

We have high protein, lower carb recipes that help your cat stay strong and fit; recipes formulated for cats with food sensitivities and specific dietary needs; and recipes that provide preventative care to keep cats healthy for life.

GO!™ recipes are prepared with a balanced blend of premium quality protein from chicken, turkey, salmon, duck and trout; plus fruits, veggies, herbs and berries. GO!™ is available in whole grain and grain free recipes, and has zero growth hormones, by-products, or artificial preservatives.

Fit + Free

Maximum meat protein with zero grains or gluten.

Premium-quality meat proteins are the first 6 ingredients in GO! FIT + FREE™. In fact, FIT + FREE has the most meat of any GO! recipe. A protein-rich, lower carb diet helps your cat stay strong, healthy, and fit. All life stage recipes are available

Sensitivity + Shine

For cats with food sensitivities and specific dietary needs.

GO! SENSITIVITY + SHINE™ recipes are great for all cats, but were formulated especially for cats with specific dietary needs and food sensitivities. All life stage recipes for cats are carefully prepared with select meat proteins, unique carbs, and essential omega oils.

Product Description:
CRANIMALS™ ORIGINAL is made from certified organic cranberries. Cranberries contain proanthocyanidins (PAC's) which inhibit the adhesion of Escherichia coli, the bacteria responsible for 80-90% of urinary tract infections. CRANIMALS™ ORIGINAL is especially suited for animals with poor kidney function or urinary tract problems. PAC's may support dental health by discouraging the growth of plaque on teeth and gums. The phytochemicals found in cranberries are also anti-carcinogenic, anti-angiogenic, anti-inflammatory, anti-bacterial, anti-viral and antioxidant. CRANIMALS™ ORIGINAL can be easily added to your pet's daily diet to boost health and vitality! Cranimals Original is also recommended to help prevent the recurrence of struvite stones.

INSTRUCTIONS:

Simply mix CRANIMALS™ ORIGINAL with your pet's kibble or wet food or add to snacks (i.e. yoghurt).

  • Small dogs or cats - 1 teaspoon/day
  • Dogs > 25kg - 2 teaspoons/day
  • Dogs > 50kg - 2.5 teaspoons/day

INGREDIENTS:

Certified organic cranberry extract

CRANIMALS™ VERY BERRY is made from certified organic blueberries, cranberries, and red raspberries, three of the world's healthiest fruits. Scientific studies show that the polyphenols in these berries have anti-carcinogenic, anti-angiogenic, anti-inflammatory, anti-bacterial, and anti-viral properties. Anthocyanidins found in cranberries and blueberries naturally support urinary tract and oral health in companion animals. Red raspberries are particularly enriched in ellagitannins, compounds demonstrated to destroy various cancer cells. CRANIMALS™ VERY BERRY delivers a synergistic combination of antioxidants, to help mop up harmful oxidants called free radicals, which damage cells, tissues and arteries, leading to chronic disease. CRANIMALS™ VERY BERRY can be easily added to your pet's daily diet for a powerful burst of extra antioxidants!

INSTRUCTIONS:

Simply mix CRANIMALS™ VERY BERRY with your pet's kibble or wet food or add to snacks (i.e. yoghurt).

  • Small dogs or cats - 1 teaspoon/day
  • Dogs > 25kg - 2 teaspoons/day
  • Dogs > 50kg - 2.5 teaspoons/day

INGREDIENTS:

Certified organic cranberry, blueberry and raspberry extract.

Cranimals™ VIBE is a wholefood supplement especially for adult dogs. It provides a nutrient synergy of cranberry and algae derived antioxidants (anthocyanidins, phycocyanin, chlorophyll, beta carotene) and vegetarian DHA Omega 3. Cranimals™ VIBE contains spirulina, a green aglal superfood that has shown potential to help limit muscle damage during heavy exercise, while DHA Omega 3 may also help increase oxygen delivery and energy utilization. Cranimals™ VIBE helps also to support kidney, liver, brain, eye and skin health through detoxification while working to mitigate inflammatory damage. Works best in tandem with liquid supplement Cranimals™ SPORT. 

INSTRUCTIONS:

Simply mix CRANIMALS™ VIBE with your pet's kibble or wet food or add to snacks (i.e. yoghurt).

  • Small dogs or cats - 1 teaspoon/day
  • Dogs > 25kg - 2 teaspoons/day
  • Dogs > 50kg - 2.5 teaspoons/day

INGREDIENTS:

Cranberry extract powder, dried seaweed meal powder, organic spirulina powder

Swheat Scoop’s story began more than 20 years ago, when a family from Detroit Lakes, Minn., set out to create a litter that would be safer for cats, people and the environment.

Today, Swheat Scoop® is run by parent company Pet Care Systems, an environmentally focused company that uses secondary wheat from across the Midwest to source its products.

Swheat Scoop natural clumping litter is available throughout North America and in more than 25 countries worldwide. It’s earth-friendly, 100 percent biodegradable and safe for everyone in the house.
